$interpreted: Tindooimu: This echo... looks like a long way down...
Jiyanama: But there's no other way out!
Tindoiimu: I bet it's no coincidence that the bridge collapsed.
Tindoiimu: This must all be part of a test...
Tindoiimu: Look at these pillars...
Jiyanama: They're so narrow...
Jiyanama: Impossible to hold us both...
Tindoiimu: Maybe that's the point. Only one of us can go.
Jiyanama: But that's too dangerous! Princess, you can't!
Tindoiimu: But we can't stay here and starve to death.
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama, please wait for me.
Jiyanama: Princess! Wait!
Tindoiimu: That music... is this an illusion?
Tindoiimu: What...!?
Tindoiimu: (There's no road...)
Tindoiimu: (Not giving me much time to think, here...)
Tindoiimu: (...This music... Oh right, it's the Seven Star Melody!)
Tindoiimu: (So the solution has to do with the stars? But my astrology is terrible... time to guess!)
Tindoiimu: Don't fail me now!
Tindoiimu: Whew... that was close!
Tindoiimu: (...Was that it? I thought the trials were supposed to be way harder than that...)
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama, you can cross now!
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama, can you hear me?
Tindoiimu: (This place is different than before! Where's the bridge?)
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama! Where are you!? Answer me!
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama, can you hear...
Tindoiimu: ...Butter? You want to come out?
Tindoiimu: Is something up with this wall?
Tindoiimu: A secret room?
Tindoiimu: Writing on the wall? What beautiful markings...
Tindoiimu: "...I've lost again... Father will be furious...
Tindoiimu: I don't know how long he'll keep me locked in here this time... mother will surely cry...
Tindoiimu: ...I'm sorry. I'm not good enough... It's so dark... so cold..."
Tindoiimu: Was this written by someone who failed the test? Looks like he drew up some solutions to the illusions.
Tindoiimu: ...Weird, these look way more complicated than the one I had to do.
Jiyanama: Help me!!
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama!?
Jiyanama: Help!
Tindoiimu: There's... two of you!?
Jiyanama?: Princess, please help your poor old Nana!
Jiyanama?: No, Princess, don't listen to her. Run!
Tindoiimu: Alliance beheadings... a mirror... more illusions...
Tindoiimu: Light... are we at the exit!?
Jiyanama: Princess... how could you tell which was the real me?
Tindoiimu: Because I... choose to believe that to the real Jiyanama, I'm not just a liability.
Tindoiimu: But that she cares about me, like one of her own children...
Jiyanama: Child...
Tindoiimu: The real enemy here is the Alliance. I shouldn't have yelled at you before. Forgive me.
Jiyanama: ...I should be the one apologizing. I should not have treated you the way I did.
Jiyanama: But when I looked upon you, I could only think of my son. I couldn't even be with him when he died...
Tindoiimu: ......
Jiyanama: I... I couldn't help myself. I knew that revenge would only bring harm to the Insect Tribe.
Tindoiimu: ...Nana...
Jiyanama: And I can't help but think of all the Alliance troops I've hurt. Do they not also have mothers, like me?
Jiyanama: Every time I close my eyes, there is only death. Death with no end in sight.
Tindoiimu: ......
Jiyanama: And I... I mourn for them. But... who is there to mourn for my child... *sob*...
Tindoiimu: I know... I know... Cry, Nana. Let it all out.
Jiyanama: *sniff* Faayida... Oh, Faayida...
